                "paragraphTitle": "What's in your carry-on bag?",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "Three travel experts talk about the things in their carry-on bag when they go on a plane."
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 2,
                "paragraphTitle": "Bruce",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "I don't carry a lot of luggage when I go on a plane. My bag is very small. I have a bottle of water and tissues. That's it. I buy the water at the airport once I am through security. I usually sleep on a plane."
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 3,
                "paragraphTitle": "Wei",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "I never use a suitcase. I put everything in my carryon bag, so there's no need to wait at baggage claim. My carry-on bag is very heavy, but that's OK. I have two watches. I wear one and I put one in my bag, so I always know what time it is at home. I travel to lots of countries. I just want to get off the plane and leave the airport as soon as I can."
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 4,
                "paragraphTitle": "Elif",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "I always have a laptop and my phone in my carry-on bag when I go on a plane. I usually have an umbrella and my keys. Flying is a good time to do my work. I can relax at home."
                ]
              }
            ],
